We could add some test in `cross` since this is implemented using the compiler? We could reuse them later for Scala 3 and we can create a lot of smaller cases.

For example:
```scala
object Main extends App {
  val name: Option[String] = Option("Tom")
  name match {
    case Some(name) => println("Hello! " + name)
    case None =>
  }
}
```
This one seem particulary weird, since we get range on `case Some(name) => println("Hello! " + name)` and then with whitespaces before.

Is that maybe a tree node that we can skip?

